The paper proposes an end-to-end 3-D object detection and tracking network using machine learning-based multi-object tracking (MOT) frameworks for 3-D point clouds. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing techniques, which are associated with the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
